"Kennedy" is a news panel show hosted by Kennedy Montgomery. Kennedy Montgomery is a libertarian that you may recognize from 90's MTV, Stossel, and the Independents.

_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2_,-'2

Kennedy is back and all moved into New York. She does her monologue on the sinking ship that is Greece.

Tonight's panel is JIMMY FAILLA, WILL RAHN, and CARRIE SHEFFIELD. Bernie Sanders applauds Greece's anti-austerity vote, promises to raise taxes if he's elected. Chris Christie resumes attacks on Rand Paul. He's mad that Paul filibustered the Patriot Act.

The panel returns to talk about how Hillary's campaign lasso'd a big ol' bunch of journalists. She continues to avoid the media, even if it takes a little rope.

Marine Biologist CRAIG O'CONNELL is here to talk about shark attacks in South Carolina. They also discuss his show "Shark Island." An island with an unusually high occurrence  of shark attacks. It also turns out that sharks hate magnets.

TOPICAL STORM:
Premature celebration leads to egg on runners face.
Abbey the french bulldog makes mess, feels guilty.
23 year old gets locked out of house by friends. He drunkenly decides the chimeny would be a good way to get back in.
Adidas makes shoes entirely made of ocean garbage.
Squirrel rides water skis.

The panel returns to talk about Michael Eisner's recent comments about beautiful women not being funny. Will Rahn is made fun of. Mommy blogger calls out weddings that don't allow kids. 

PEREZ HILTON is in studio to talk about Donald Trump, Oprah running for president, Caitlyn Jenner getting criticized for her fashion sense.

Nightcap: U.S. women win the world cup!
